I just rebuilt mine with all Moog part and I couldn't be happier. Moog is known for their quality and that's what I put on all my cars. They're not the cheapest, but they're also not the most expensive. You'll have to piece it together or else you'll pay a premium through some online vendor for them to have put it together. It's pretty straight forward. There are plenty of posts on here where people have assembled parts lists for this project. One thing to note is that the original ball joints were riveted in, so you'll have to get an angle grinder with a cutoff wheel into some tight spaces. I did mine with the front end off of the truck, so I can't help you there.

KUALA LUMPUR (Dec 17): Hong Leong Investment Bank (HLIB) Research expects property developers to continue facing a tough operating environment in 2021, with developers cautiously carrying out launches and offering discounts on their products. The research house's analyst Lim Ken Wern said in a note today that with the Home Ownership Campaign (HOC) ending on May 31 next year, developers will need to continue providing goodies in order to attract bookings. â€œOur channel check revealed that listed developers are garnering a sales conversion rate of about 50% and that some buyers still struggle to obtain their desired financing from banks,â€ he said. Nonetheless, given the low-base impact of 2020, he said 2021 may potentially see improved transaction volumes when the economy recovers from the ongoing Covid-19 pandemic. However, Lim noted that residential transaction volumes in the third quarter of 2020 (3Q20) showed 55,845 units being transacted, of which 62.2% were for houses priced below RM300,000, which provided minimal margins for listed developers. The number of overhang residential units stood at 30,926 units in 3Q20, according to the latest data available, up by 212% from 9,903 units back in 2015, of which 45.1% of the units were priced above RM500,000. High-rise units accounted for 54.2% of total overhang units, while two- and three-storey terraced houses made up 27.8%, he said. According to Lim, monthly residential property loan applications and loan approvals were down year-on-year (y-o-y) for the cumulative first nine-month period (9M20) by 5.5% and 25.9% respectively, showing a decrease in the approval rate of 21.6% largely due to the impact of the movement control order (MCO) earlier in the year. Meanwhile, Lim said, in the latest results reported, three out of six property companies under his coverage came in within expectations, while IOI Properties Group Bhd and S P Setia Bhd came in above expectations, and UEM Sunrise Bhd disappointed. â€œBetter-than-expected sales and progressive billing recognitions contributed to the performance of IOIPG (IOI Properties Group) and S P Setia, while higher-than-expected operating cost resulted in the disappointment from UEM Sunrise,â€ he said. Sales figures in the recent results release showed that on average, companies were on track for their respective full-year sales targets with the exception of UEM Sunrise, said Lim. He, however, maintained his "neutral" stance on the property sector due to the ongoing weak property market environment. â€œOn the other hand, a potential economic recovery in 2021, coupled with undemanding valuations (coverage universe price-to-book value at 0.5 times or more than two standard deviations [2SD] below the five-year mean) should lend some support to the downside,â€ he said. â€œWe lower our revalued net asset value discounts by 5% on counters which we had aggressively placed discounts of over 80% (i.e. S P Setia and UEM Sunrise, with the 'hold' calls maintained) to reflect the positive sentiment on a recovery play,â€ he said. For top picks, he continued to like Sunway Bhd ("buy"; target price [TP]: RM1.95) as an underappreciated property-construction conglomerate with mature investment properties, a growing trading and quarry division, and potential monetisation of its healthcare business. He also likes Matrix Concept Holdings Bhd ("buy"; TP: RM2.11) as it rides on the affordable housing theme within its successful townships with cheap land cost and sustained property sales, coupled with future potential job flows from its Indonesian venture. â€œIts dividend yield of over 6% remains one of the highest in the sector,â€ said Lim.

mrclubbie wrote: Driver of BMW in Tanjong Pagar crash and passengers identified https://www.straitstimes.com/singapo...ers-identified SINGAPORE - Details have emerged on three of the five men who died in an accident in Tanjong Pagar on Saturday (Feb 13) morning as messages of shock and condolences poured in from friends and family on social media. The men were in a car which slammed into the front of a vacant shophouse and burst into flames at about 5.40am. The driver of the BMW M4 coupe is believed to be Mr Jonathan Long, 29, while two of his passengers have been identified as Mr Gary Wong Hong Chieh, 29, and Mr Eugene Yap, 29. Mr Wong and Mr Long were long-time friends, according to social media posts. The Straits Times understands that the two other passengers who died in the crash were Mr Elvin Tan Yong Hao, 28, and Mr Teo Qi Xiang, 26. A 26-year-old woman, believed to be known to Mr Long, had attempted to assist him and the passengers after the accident. She suffered severe burns to her body and was taken to Singapore General Hospital. Eugene Yap According to previous media reports, Mr Yap was a co-founder of the local bubble tea chain Bober Tea. His Instagram profile also said that he was a wealth manager with Aviva Financial Advisers. Social media posts showed that he and Mr Long were on a trip to the United States together in February last year. Mr Yap was also pictured with sports cars and supercars in some of these posts. According to a report by ChannelNewsAsia in August last year, Mr Yap opened the first Bober Tea store here in June 2018 with co-founders Mr Joseph Oh and Mr Gabriel Kok. Since then, the homegrown label has expanded in Singapore to eight outlets, with franchises also opening in Manila and California. Gary Wong According to his social media profiles, Mr Wong had studied IT at the Singapore Management University before starting a career in financial services. He was also involved in volunteer work during the Covid-19 pandemic last year. In a Facebook post in May last year, Mr Wong said he and Mr Long had bought thousands of face masks for distribution to needy families. "Packing everything was really tiring but it will be worth it after all. Stay safe everyone, Covid-19 will be over sooner or later," the caption read. A Facebook user, who identified herself as Mr Wong's sister, wrote on Saturday: "My beloved brother Gary was killed this morning. He had a big heart... (cared) for his family and loved to help the needy. But this morning, God took him away from us." Jonathan Long Mr Long also worked for Aviva Financial Advisers as a senior financial services manager, according to his social media profiles. In some photos, Mr Long, who graduated from RMIT University at the SIM Global Education campus with an economics and finance degree, can also be seen posing with sports cars, including a blue BMW. sister used the word killed instead of passed away/died.

SINGAPORE â€“ Five people died and one was sent to Singapore General Hospital after a car slammed into the front of a shophouse on Saturday (Feb 13) morning. In a statement to The Straits Times, the SCDF said it was alerted to a fire at 37 Tanjong Pagar Rd at about 5.40am. â€œThe fire involved a car and the front of a shophouse. SCDF extinguished the fire with three water jets and one compressed air foam backpack. Five people were pronounced dead at the scene and one sent to SGH with burn injuries. ST understands that the five who died were in the car when the accident happened. ST understands the car was a BMW. The cause of the fire is under investigation. When ST arrived at the scene at 7.50am, about 200m of Tanjong Pagar Road was cordoned off. The Land Transport Authority announced a road closure on Tanjong Pagar Road (towards Murray Street) after Maxwell Road at 7.30am. SBS Transit said that bus services 80 and 145 were being diverted from Tanjong Pagar Road (towards Hoe Chiang Road), with 10 bus stops skipped due to an accident. This article was first published in The Straits Times

Voor ons 25 jarig jubileum wilde ik en mijn vrouw een weekend weg. Dit is de katjeskelder geworden. Bij aankomst bij het huisje ging de deur niet open. Ze hadden ons de verkeerde kaart gegeven. Na een uur wachten konden we eindelijk binnen maar dit was een deceptie. De woonkamer stonk naar canabis en het toilet was niet gepoets, heel erg vies. Toen we 's avonds op het park gingen eten gooie een ober een dienblad over mijn vrouw. Hij bood niet eens zijn excuses aan! In de nacht was er heel harde muziek en luid geschreeuw uit een naburig huisje. We hebben geklaagd maar daar niets van terug gehoord. De herrie heeft tot 4 uur in de nacht geduurd. We waren helemaal uitgeput na dit weekend. Ons jubileum weekend was verpest en met ons lage inkomen zit een vakantie er de komende tijd niet meer in. Erg jammer dat roompot met onze klacht niets heeft gedaan en zelfs afdeed als onzin. We zullen hier nooit meer terug gaan!

Biopharma stocks advanced in the week ended Feb. 5, driven higher by a slew of catalysts. Large-cap pharma earnings, vaccine updates, M&A activity, IPO news flow and follow-on offerings all served to lift stocks higher. In an unexpected move, Jazz Pharmaceuticals PLC (NASDAQ: JAZZ) agreed to buy plant-derived cannabinoid drug maker GW Pharmaceuticals PLC- ADR (NASDAQ: GWPH) for $7.2 billion. Novavax, Inc. (NASDAQ: NVAX) shares found follow-up buying interest amid vaccine updates. Earnings from large-cap biopharma companies can at best be qualified as mixed. The IPO calendar of the week was heavy, with 10 healthcare stocks making their Wall Street debuts this week. (NASDAQ: IMGN) (before the market open) IPOs Adagene, Inc., a China-based, clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company developing antibody-based cancer immunotherapies, has filed to offer 7.354 million ADSs, representing 9,1925 million ordinary shares, in an initial public offering. The company expects to price the offering in the $17-$19 range, and has applied for listing its ADSs on the Nasdaq under the ticker symbol ADAG. French clinical-stage biotech Biophytis S.A., which focuses on development of therapeutics that slow the degenerative processes associated with aging, is proposing to offer 1.2 million ADSs in an IPO. Each ADS represents the right to receive 10 ordinary shares. The offering price is expected to be between $15 and $18 per ADS. The company has applied to list its ADSs on the Nasdaq under the ticker symbol BPTS. Longeveron LLC, a clinical stage biotech developing cellular therapies for specific aging-related and life-threatening conditions, is offering 2.73 million shares at an estimated price range of $10-$12. The Miami, Florida-based company has applied for listing the shares on the Nasdaq under the ticker symbol LGVN. Durham, North Carolina-based Bioventus Inc. is planning a 7.53-million-share IPO, with the offering estimated to be priced between $16 and 18 apiece. The medical device company has applied for listing its shares on the Nasdaq under the ticker symbol BVS. La malattia di Fabry Ã¨ una malattia rara che si manifesta in genere durante l'infanzia con alcuni sintomi aspecifici tra cui sensazioni dolorose alle estremitÃ  degli arti, comparsa di macchie rossastre sulla pelle, sudorazione ridotta, opacitÃ  della cornea, dolore neuropatico, manifestazioni gastrointestinali, tinnito (fischio o ronzio nell'orecchio) e perdita di udito, angiocheratomi (lesioni della pelle), ritardo della crescita e della pubertÃ . Proprio per la sua raritÃ  e per i sintomi, che spesso sono aspecifici e facilmente confondibili con altre patologie, in molti pazienti la diagnosi arriva tardi. Le complicazioni in etÃ  adulta comprendono soprattutto la patologia renale cronica, cardiomiopatia, complicazioni del sistema nervoso centrale, inclusi infarto prematuro e morte prematura. La qualitÃ  della vita dei pazienti risulta quindi fortemente compromessa. Fortunatamente, una diagnosi precoce, insieme all'adozione di una terapia adeguata, rappresentano un aiuto concreto per gestire al meglio la patologia, trattarne efficacemente i sintomi e scongiurare danni irreparabili a organi vitali Nel corso della vita, la malattia colpisce diversi organi e sistemi, dal sistema nervoso, reni, cuore, vasi sanguigni. Si puÃ² arrivare a situazioni gravi come l'insufficienza renale, l'infarto o l'ictus. Le terapie enzimatiche sostitutive a disposizione sono due, agalsidasi beta e agalsidasi alfa , e hanno permesso di allungare la durata media della vita, che altrimenti sarebbe di circa 50 anni nei maschi e 60 nelle femmine, reintegrando l'enzima mancante o deficitario per poter eliminare il substrato accumulatosi nei tessuti degli organi e, quindi, prevenire o stabilizzare il processo di declino funzionale nei diversi organi bersaglio Alcuni studi hanno evidenziato la maggiore soliditÃ  e robustezza dei dati di efficacia a livello renale di agalsidasi beta rispetto ad agalsidasi alfa . Il dato significativo che emerge da questi studi Ã¨ il deterioramento dei parametri renali, misurato come la velocitÃ  di filtrazione glomerulare stimata (eGFR), nei pazienti trattati con una dose inferiore di agalsidasi beta o con il dosaggio standard di agalsidasi alfa e un aumento dei sintomi gastrointestinali che fanno parte della storia naturale della patologia. Le riduzioni annuali dell'eGFR risultavano invece attenuate nei pazienti che sono in trattamento con la dose standard di agalsidasi beta. Oggi, per la prima volta, i dati di confronto tra le due terapie, che sottolineano la maggiore efficacia almeno a livello renale di agalsidasi beta rispetto ad agalsidasi alfa , sono stati inseriti nella scheda tecnica di agalsidasi beta. Ãˆ stato infatti effettuato di recente un importante aggiornamento all'interno della scheda tecnica di agalsidasi beta, inserendo per la prima volta i dati di comparazione dell'efficacia con agalsidasi alfa.

Afgelopen zomer hebben we via touroperator 'Masies Carmen' geboekt. Omdat we in veel reviews al negatieve verhalen lazen over de steile, in slechte staat zijnde, oprit hebben we van tevoren navraag gedaan bij de touroperator. We kregen letterlijk te horen dat er nog nooit klachten waren geweest. Met de kennis van nu kunnen we zeggen dat dat niet waar is. Er is heel veel over geklaagd, bij verschillende touroperators. En terecht, want de oprit is zeer slecht. Heel steil maar als hij in goede staat zou zijn is dat wel te doen. Maar het gewapende beton brokkelt al jaren af waardoor de ijzeren pinnen eruit en omhoog steken. Levensgevaarlijk! Al jaren bekend maar de eigenaar (Fam Carmen Weijers) doet er niets aan. Verder gevaarlijke, slechte staat van electra: open draden in de tuin. Daardoor geen buiten- en zwembadverlichting en vaak kortsluiting. We hebben een hele middag zonder stroom gezeten en Milli (beheerder) kwam pas laat en deed niets.

A woman in her 50s has suffered suspected spinal injuries after falling from a horse on January 10. The Bundaberg-based RACQ LifeFlight Rescue helicopter airlifted the seriously injured woman after the crew was sent to a private property, north west of Bundaberg, at 12:40pm. Local Queensland Ambulance Service (QAS) paramedics initially treated the patient, before the rescue helicopter arrived. It's believed the woman had been mustering cattle, when the horse she was riding was spooked and threw her off. The patient was treated for suspected spinal injuries and subsequently airlifted to Bundaberg Hospital, in a serious but stable condition.

Alla c. a. Della Direzione. Non sono sicuro se avete ricevuro il mio e-mail del giorno 3/06/19. Sto inviando un altro e vi sicuro che non aspetto vs risposta. Mi imaggino che la vergonia non vi permette do rispondere. Devo solo precisare il fatti di questa aventura con la macchina noleggiata da voi. Il giorno 30/05/2019 ho noleggiato da Ecovia al aeroporto di Bologna una auto Seat MII Eco Fuel secondo contratto RA 349151. Sono abituato noleggiare le macchine sempre con serbatoio pieno, sono le norme standard in tutta la Europa. Con vs macchina sono andato a loc. Pantiere vicino Urbino, distanza 161 km. Giorno successivo dovevo andare a Urbino dove avevamo un matrimonio famigliare. Dopo aver partito da Tenuta Santi Giacomo e Filippo verso Urbino dopo 5 km la macchina si ha fermata a mezzo campagna. Per 2 ore ho provato telefonare al numero indicato nel contratto (diecine di prove) nessuno rispondeva. Finalmente si fermato un uomo gentile sulla bici il quale con telefono a mano faceva consulenze con suo amico di una autoofficina. Hanno constatato che ambedue serbatoi cono â€seccchiâ€. A questo punto gentile uomo ha chiesto suo amico di venire con la bombola di metano sul posto dove si ha fermata la maccina. Specialista e venuto con metano, ha carricato serbatoio e mi accompagnato al distributore dove potutto fare pieno benzina e metano. Tutta questa avventura durava 3 ore. Ho perso la ceremonia di matrimonio per quale siamo venuti in Italia con mia moglie. Ho pagato per intervento tecnico piu metano 75 â‚¬, piu riempimento a distributore (e normale). Il tecnico mi ha spiegato che due serbatoi non erranno pieni - macchina si ha fermata dopo 165-170 km! Io non sono abbitoato alla macchina di questo tipo, nessuno mi ha detto che serbatoi non sono pieni. Nessuno mi ch detto che distributore di metano non si trova su ogni stazione di rifornimento. Tutto sommato mi sento fregato. Lascio senza commento â€discorsoâ€ con vs dipendente in ufficio di aeroporto di Bologna. Secondo lui era colpa mia! Io ho 70 anni e meta della mi vita ho passato viaggiando in diversi paesi, maggior parte in Italia usano macchine di noleggio. Mai avuto un caso cosi arrogane e vergoniozo come questo. Ho lasciato la macchina al aeroporto di Bologna con serbatoio di bezina pieno e metano 1/2. Non affito mai piu la macchina da voi nel futuro. Saluti

ZzerosS posted... Youâ€™re telling that being a game dev is so hard but the people working in those Nestle factories have it easy? Each item in your poll should say â€œGive me my X, no matter the cost to human life and suffering.â€ Out of those 4 things being made, devs suffer the least by far. Until you've actually done both jobs you don't know what you're talking about. I'd take working extra hours in a physically demanding job any day over working extra hours as a developer. The physical exhaustion from 10+ hour days doing construction (did this for two years) or working in a 110+ degree kitchen (did this for four and a half years) was much easier to deal with than the mental exhaustion from 10+ hour days doing development (going on year five). If the pay was anywhere close to being equal I'd quit my job as a developer today and go back to one of those two physically demanding jobs. All of that said, crunch can, and should, be avoided in most instances if management isn't terrible and they have the resources available

Agensi Kawalan Sempadan Malaysia (AKSEM) berjaya merampas 4,500 karton rokok putih bernilai RM742,500 termasuk nilai cukai. Ia hasil penahanan sebuah lori tiga tan membawa muatan barangan plastik dan tilam di Kilometer 177.3 Lebuhraya Utara-Selatan berhampiran Butterworth, pukul 10.30 malam tadi. Menurut Komander AKSEM, Asisten Superintendan Mohd Khairi Abdullah, rampasan dibuat hasil maklumat diperoleh pihaknya. Lori dipandu lelaki berusia 31 tahun itu dipercayai dari Kuala Lumpur menuju ke utara dan menemukan 90 kotak mengandungi 4,500 karton rokok putih yang tidak dibayar cukai kastam. AKSEM yakin sebahagian rokok sudah diserahkan kepada penerima di Pulau Pinang manakala bakinya 90 kotak dipercayai untuk pasaran sekitar Kedah. MENINGGALKAN SUATU JAWAPAN

Mooi hotel in een rustige wijk, een klein stukje lopen van de hoofdstraat van Marrakech. Het ontbijt is op het dakterras en behoorlijk uitgebreid: als je geluk hebt, heb je een plekje buiten. De kamers zijn zeer verschillend: van zeer luxe (bed+canope+bank) naar twee persoonsbed, naar drie eenpersoons, maar dan wel weer met balkon. Ieder wat wilt. Badkamer is oke, jammer dat je moet douchen in het bad. Avondeten is geweldig! Heerlijk, goed gevarieerd en uitgebreid. Personeel is aardig en probeert je bij alles te helpen.

Mohd Firdaus Esa Panjangkan Konsesi TOL 20 tahun dan tidak menjual TOL ke syarikat swasta Mula2 aku tak setuju tetapi penulisan dari Ipoh Mali nampak ada kebaikan utk rakyat,baru aku faham Kenapa sambung 20 Tahun tempoh Konsesi..? Pertama Kerajaan mahu mengelakkan dari Kerajaan terpaksa membayar pampasan berbillion Ringgit kepada Syarikat Konsesi seperti mana zaman BN.. Duit Berbillion Ringit itu boleh dikembalikan untuk Manfaat Kerajaan dan rakyat.. Zaman BN dulu kerajaan bayar Pampasan Berbillion Setahun, Bukan saja depa tak turunkan harga Tol, Malah ditambah tempoh Konsesi.. Kedua, memanjangkan tempoh konsesi ini Adalah Faktor prospek Pelaburan dan kepentingan PLUS... Andainya Kerajaan mengumumkan tidak disambung Konsesi tersebut dalam keadaan Kerajaan tidak membayar pampasan.. Keyakinan pasaran akan hilang.. nilai dan prospek keuntungan Saham Plus dan Syarikat berkaitan akan jatuh teruk.. manakala kesannya kepada Pegangan tabung Haji, KWSP dan PNB , yang akhirnya akan menyebabkan pulangan dividen pedeposit mereka akan terjejas teruk.. Kalau diibaratkan PLUS Holding itu adalah rumah dan Ladang kita.. Hak milik, Title Geran tu tetap milik kita... Tetapi kalau dijual kepada Maju Holding, RJJ dan Widad Group..Kita dah hilang suara dan hak keatas aset dan hasil perniagaan kita...Apa manfaatnya.. Kerajaan diumpamakan hanya melakukan Rifinance rumah sendiri, memanjangkan tempoh Pinjaman..dalam keadaan kita dapat Manfaat dari Modal perniagaan dan bayaran bulanan yang rendah.. dan Kelebihan Tunai kepada Kerajaan untuk dipulangkan kepada rakyat... hakikatnya rumah dan ladang itu kekal milik kita.. Pada masa akan datang..Bila kita/ Kerajaan ada Kemampuan.. kita akan tetap dapat semula pemilikan Penuh atas rumah Tersebut...2-3 tahun, Atau 10 tahun lagi.. kalau kewangan kerajaan baik, Kerajaan boleh saja gunakan rezab Tunainya untuk membeli semua Kepentingan.. atau memberikan ianya secara percuma.. Berbeza kalau ianya Dijual.. Sebab Apa, PM dan Menteri Kewangan ada kuasa keatas pelaburan Khazanah dan KWSP... Projek RTP DUN Simanggang berjalan lancar - Francis Harden PROJEK-projek RTP di kawasan ADUN Simanggang Datuk Francis Harden Hollis, yang juga merupakan Menteri Muda Kesejahteraan Komuniti berjalan dengan lancar. Francis berkata demikian kepada pemberita setelah mengadakan lawatan meninjau progres projek yang telah diluluskan dibawah projek RTP semalam. Antara projek-projek yang dilawati beliau adalah pembinaan baru jalan akses sepanjang 3.8KM menghubungkan Rumah Sanggau, Sungai Reboh dengan Rumah Wiss, Paku Ili dan Projek Jambatan Gantung Rumahh Sherit, Titikah termasuk pembinaan Concrete Culvert. Difahamkan juga, status projek bagi pembinaan jalan dari Sungai Reboh ke Paku Ili dengan kos RM500,000 telah siap sepenuhnya. Beliau juga menjelaskan, jambatan gantung di Kampung Titikah dan Concrete Culvert sedang dalam pembinaan dan dijangka siap pada akhir Disember 2020. Francis juga melawat tapak cadangan membina Jambatan Gantung Rumah Sanggau menyeberangi Sungai Batang Undop. "Permohonan dari penduduk kampung merupakan manifestasi harapan terhadap kerajaan GPS yang terbukti menunaikan janji dalam setiap permohonan yang dikemukakan," katanya. Tambah Francis lagi, penduduk kawasan Ulu Undop sangat bertuah kerana kerajaan sentiasa mendengar permintaan mereka dan tingkat perubahan kemajuan infrastruktur amat ketara jika dibandingkan dari zaman dahulu. "Hanya tinggal usaha sendiri untuk mempergunakan kemudahan yang disediakan maka penduduk janganlah memperjudikan nasib mereka menyokong parti pembangkang yang sekarang ini giat menjalankan propaganda mempengaruhi rakyat kawasan luar bandar." "Banyak janji yang ditabur namun kesudahannya mereka tidak berdaya menunaikan janji dengan mengemukakan pelbagai alasan," katanya lagi. Pesannya lagi, usah membuat kesilapan dalam memilih kerana wakil rakyat sedia ada sangat cemerlang dan tidak perlu mencari pengganti buat masa sekarang kerana pembangunan yang rancak sekarang hasil pelan jangka panjang kerajaan GPS yang didukung oleh ADUN dan jemaah menteri. Posted on 20 Oct 2020 22:02:27AddThis Sharing Buttons Empat lelaki yang terbabit dalam video viral di mana dua daripadanya memaki hamun anggota polis dihadapkan ke Mahkamah Majistret Slim River di atas pertuduhan menghalang penjawat awam menjalankan tugas. Pertuduhan dibacakan dalam Bahasa Melayu, namun tertuduh, P Panneerselvan, 32, S Vijandran, 41, A Sivakumar, 28, dan R Durai Raaj, 25, tidak memahami pertuduhan tersebut. Berdasarkan pertuduhan, kesemua tertuduh didakwa menghalang Koperal Muhd Syahrul Azuwan Abd Manaf dari menjalankan tugasnya dengan sengaja tidak memberi kerjasama setelah diberi amaran berulang kali untuk beredar, serta gagal mengemukakan kad pengenalan. Kesemua tertuduh melakukan kesalahan itu di tepi jalan berdekatan Plaza Tol Slim River pada jam 3.30 pagi, 16 Oktober 2020. BACA LAPORAN BERKAITAN: Kesemua tertuduh didakwa mengikut Seksyen 186 Kanun Keseksaan dan Seksyen 34 akta yang sama jika sabit kesalahan boleh dihukum penjara dua tahun atau denda maksimum RM10,000 atau kedua-duanya sekali. Majistret Nurul Hidayah Ismail membenarkan semua tertuduh diikat jamin RM3,000 dengan seorang penjamin dan kes disebut semula pada 26 Oktober ini bagi mendapatkan jurubahasa Tamil. Duraj Raaj juga didakwa menggunakan kekerasan jenayah dengan menolak badan dan membuka zip 'vest'Muhd Syahrul semasa kejadian dan didakwa mengikut Seksyen 353 Kanun Keseksaan yang membawa hukuman penjara dua tahun atau denda atau kedua-duanya sekali jika sabit kesalahan. Mahkamah juga membenarkan tertuduh diikat jamin RM2,500 dengan seorang penjamin dan menetapkan tarikh yang sama untuk sebutan semula kes. Pendakwaan dikendalikan oleh Timbalan Pendakwa Raya Nur Diyana Zubir, manakala kesemua tertuduh diwakili peguam Yayasan Bantuan Guaman Kebangsaan, A Puvanasvary. :

, Jakarta â€“ Semenjak masa pandemi. Bukalapak menerapkan strategi menjadi perusahaan yang sustainable untuk terus menjalankan misinya. KabarUang.com Misinya yakni menciptakan perekonomian yang adil bagi semua. Dengan cara menawarkan produk-produk bukalapak melalui marketplace, O2O, atau lini bisnis procurement Bukalapak. Erick Wicaksono, VP of Marketing Bukalapak mengatakan langkah yang diambil pihaknya terbukti bisa erdampak positif di masa pandemi ini. Hal itu terlihat dari kenaikan transaksi yang dimulai dari bulan Juni. â€œJumlah transaksi oleh Mitra Bukalapal di bulan Juni tahun ini juga naik hingga sekitar 3 kali lipat dari bulan yang sama tahun lalu. Kenaikan ini merupakan yang tertinggi yang pernah dicapai oleh Mitra Bukalapak,â€ ungkapnya dilansir kontan.co.id, Rabu (11/11). Bukan hanya itu, Erick mengatakan bahwa kenaikan yang terjadi pada jumlah pelaku UMKM ini bergabung menjadi Pelapak dan Mitra Bukalapak. Saat ini ada lebih dari 3 juta pada 7 bulan pertama tahun ini. Harapan Bukalapak di tahun depan Pada tahun depan, pihaknya berharap bahwa semakin banyak masyarakat yang bisa merasakan adanya inovasi dan teknologi untuk meringankan beban ekonomi akibat pandemi. â€œKami juga menyadari bahwa tahun 2021 masih menjadi tantangan khususnya terkait dampak ekonomi dari Covid-19 yang mempengaruhi daya beli beli masyarakat,â€ lanjutnya. Untuk itu, pihaknya berupaya untuk mengatur budget seefisien mungkin, memperluas market di luar tier 1, melengkapi SKU khususnya barang-barang kebutuhan pokok dan kategori yang sesuai dengan apa yang dicari masyarakat, serta memperkuat lini bisnisnya dengan Online to Offline. Selain itu juga, pihaknya akan terus mengoptimalkan platform Bukalapak agar dapat dimanfaatkan oleh elaku UMKM Indonesia untuk meningkatkan kapasitas bisnis dengan dukungan imfrasturktur Bukalapak. Diantaranya yakni dukungan logistik, metode pembayaran, pinjaman modal, fitur investasi, virtual produk hingga pelatihan serta pemberdayaan. â€œSelain itu, kami memberdayakan lini bisnis B2B kami yang memungkinkan UMKM untuk bisa ambil bagian dalam pengadaan barang dalma skala yang lebih besar dan luas,â€ paparnya. Dia juga berpendapat bahwa Bukalapak selalu terbuka dalam bekerja sama dengan sektor swasta maupun BUMN dan Pemerintah. Hal ini sesuai dengan semangat gotong royong.

Na het noodzakelijk moeten om boeken vanwege Thomas Cook besloten ipv naar Mallorca te gaan een vakantie te kiezen naar Turkije. Voor beide was het de eerste keer naar Kusadasi, leuk plaatsje met veel te doen. Helaas bleek ons vier sterren hotel absoluut zijn 4 sterren niet waardig. Eten was veel het zelfde, en vaak koud ? lauw van tempratuur. Het all Inclusive had ik mezelf ook anders voorgesteld op basis van eerdere ervaringen in Turkse hotels. Veel was op al halverwege de middag. De liften die vaak niet werkten en de housekeeping die iedere dag komt op het moment dat jij net wil gaan douchen, en dat terwijl je heel de dag van je kamer af bent. Vragen om schone handdoeken en aanvulling van toiletpapier. Voor ons is dit 1x maar nooit meer naar dit hotel. Met de mensen om ons heen wel een leuke gezellige vakantie gehad maar nogmaals het hotel is absoluut geen 4 sterren hotel. De foto's bij Vakantiediscounter komen totaal niet over een

SEREMBAN - Polis akan menjalankan siasatan secara telus berhubung dakwaan seorang anggotanya yang meminta wang daripada seorang kelindan lori dalam satu sekatan jalan raya semalam. Ketua Polis Daerah Seremban, Asisten Komisioner Mohd Said Ibrahim berkata, suspek lelaki berusia 55 tahun itu telah pun ditahan di Senawang pada jam 12 tengah hari semalam. Menurutnya, polis telah menerima laporan daripada kelindan berkenaan pada jam 9.44 pagi yang mana dia mendakwa telah ditahan semasa melalui susur tol Senawang kerana tidak dapat menunjukkan surat majikan. "Pada waktu itu, pengadu telah diminta untuk membuat bayaran dan bagi menggantikan bayaran, pengadu diminta menyerahkan bawang yang berada di dalam lorinya. "Bertindak atas maklumat, siasatan terperinci telah dijalankan dan tangkapan ke atas suspek telah dibuat pada hari sama jam 12 tengah hari di Senawang di sini," katanya. Dalam pada itu, Mohd Said berkata, kes disiasat mengikut Seksyen 384 Kanun Keseksaan kerana melakukan pemerasan dan pihaknya akan menjalankan siasatan secara terperinci tanpa sebarang kompromi serta akan mengambil tindakan sewajarnya. Terdahulu sebuah portal melaporkan seorang kelindan lori didakwa dipaksa 'meninggalkan' dua guni bawang sebelum dibenarkan melepasi sekatan jalan raya di Negeri Sembilan, Ahad lalu. Difahamkan insiden itu berlaku pada jam 2 petang, ketika lelaki berusia 26 tahun itu dan pemandu lori dalam perjalanan dari Shah Alam, Selangor untuk menghantar bawang serta ubi kentang di sekitar Seremban dan Senawang. Lori tersebut tidak dibenarkan melepasi sekatan jalan raya dekat plaza tol Senawang kerana mereka didakwa gagal menunjukkan surat kebenaran perjalanan oleh polis.

The National Australia Bank Ltd (ASX: NAB) share price has gone up by more than 9% so far in 2021. Is it a buy right now? Some brokers have had their say. What's happening right now with NAB? The NAB share price is moving about with a bit of volatility at the moment as markets react to the opposing thoughts about interest rates. On the one hand, RBA governor boss Dr Lowe said that he doesn't expect the official cash rate to rise for at least three years , unless the economy manages to recover sooner. However, before today, bond yields had been climbing . The Australian Financial Review quoted Tamar Hamlyn from Ardea Investment Management: The earlier part of the move was driven by rising inflation expectations because one of the components for bond yields is compensation for inflation. More recently, the increase in bond yields has continued and it has come about by an increase in real yields. If people think that economic growth is going to improve, then real returns â€“ economic growth after inflation â€“ are likely to improve across the entire economy because it's easier to generate positive returns when the global economy is growing. It was only a couple of weeks ago that the big four ASX bank released its FY21 first quarter update. FY21 first quarter The NAB share price responded positively after revealing it made $1.7 billion of statutory net profit and $1.65 billion of cash earnings. NAB explained that improving economic trends have been a key driver of the first quarter result, with cash earnings 47% higher than the FY20 second half quarterly average primarily driven by low credit impairment charges. The bank said that at an underlying level, performance has been sound in the current competitive, low interest rate environment. It said that it made 1% cash earnings growth compared to the first quarter of FY20. However, cash earnings before tax and credit impairment charges were down 6%. But it still isn't plain sailing yet, according to the bank's CEO, Ross McEwan, who said: Improving economic and health outcomes in Australia and New Zealand are encouraging, as are the reductions we are seeing in deferral balances. However, there are still a number of uncertainties regarding further clarity. These include the impact on customers of ongoing health alerts and measures put in place to contain the spread of COVID-19 , and the wind-down of deferral and jobkeeper programs. Supporting customers and keeping the bank safe through this period remain our priorities. Broker thoughts UBS said that its cash net profit was better than expectations due to the fact that impairment charges were lower. It was the lowest impairment charge since it started giving quarterly earnings updates over a decade ago. Its balance sheet was stronger than expected, with a common equity tier 1 (CET1) capital ratio of 11.7%. UBS has a NAB share price target of $27. Credit Suisse is another broker that has a share price target of $27 for NAB shares. The broker has decreased its expectations of bad debts for NAB, meaning it's now expecting higher profit from NAB. Both brokers think that NAB shares are currently a buy. Where to invest $1,000 right now When investing expert Scott Phillips has a stock tip, it can pay to listen. After all, the flagship Motley Fool Share Advisor newsletter he has run for more than eight years has provided thousands of paying members with stock picks that have doubled, tripled or even more.* Scott just revealed what he believes are the for investors to buy right now. These stocks are trading at dirt-cheap prices and Scott thinks they are great buys right now.

KUALA LUMPUR - Jaringan Pekerja Kontrak Kerajaan (JPKK) menggesa agar kerajaan membela nasib pekerja kontrak dan menyerap mereka yang bekerja secara kontrak di premis kerajaan sebagai pekerja tetap. Setiausaha JPKK, Sivaranjani Manickam berkata, menjadi harapan JPKK supaya pekerja-pekerja kontrak seperti pekerja pembersihan dan pengawal keselamatan di sekolah mahupun di hospital dapat diserapkan sebagai pekerja tetap. "Kami harap kerajaan dapat mengurangkan pembaziran dan tingkatkan cekapkan pentadbiran," katanya pada sidang akhbar Pelancaran Kempen Hapus Sistem Kontrak di Facebook JPKK hari ini. Sementara itu, Pegawai Perhubungan Perusahaan Kesatuan Pekerja Swasta Hospital Kerajaan (PSHK) Danaletchimi Langaswaran berkata, sistem kontrak sedia ada sangat tidak adil kepada pekerja kontrak. "Faedah pekerja kontrak yang sudah bekerja selama 20 tahun, sama sahaja dengan faedah yang diperoleh pekerja tetap baharu,â€ katanya menambah kerajaan diharap dapat mengiktiraf pekerja pembersihan sebagai 'frontliners' supaya mereka layak mendapat bantuan yang diperuntukkan dalam Belanjawan 2021. Dalam pada itu, Koordinator JPKK Johor Yusni Mahnyok yang juga seorang pengawal keselamatan berkata pekerja kontrak juga seolah-olah tidak mempunyai hak untuk bersuara meskipun telah lama bekerja. - Bernama

When designing the architecture and navigational structure of a web site, a sitemap can be extremely helpful. A sitemap can keep the navigation links organized by category, predict how any dynamic links will function, and keep the framework under control. Web developers are not the only parties involved in the process who can benefit from a well-structured sitemap. Many search engines, including Googlebot, can crawl through an XML file that contains the sitemap data to crawl and index the siteâ€™s content.

Penstrukturan kadar tol Lebuhraya Utara Selatan (PLUS) mulai 1 Feb ini merupakan kali pertama berlaku pengurangan tol dalam sejarah lebuh raya itu tanpa beban pampasan oleh kerajaan, sekali gus mewujudkan penjimatan RM26 bilion yang boleh memberi pelbagai faedah kepada rakyat dan pembangunan ekonomi. Ia merupakan â€œtriple winâ€ apabila pengguna lebuh raya akan menikmati diskaun tol sebanyak 18 peratus dengan tiadanya peningkatan kadar tol sehingga tempoh konsesi tamat pada 2038, kata Setiausaha Politik kepada Menteri Kewangan Tony Pua. Tegasnya apa yang gagal dilakukan oleh Barisan Nasional (BN) selama ini bakal ditunaikan oleh kerajaan Pakatan Harapan (PH). Sambil mengingatkan bekas Perdana Menteri Datuk Seri Najib Tun Razak mengenai dasar lebuh raya PLUS di bawah kerajaan BN yang sering menyaksikan peningkatan kadar tol, Pua berkata pada zaman BN kerajaan terpaksa membayar pampasan lebih RM3 bilion kepada konsesi untuk membekukan kadar tol. "Nampaknya bekas Perdana Menteri Datuk Seri Najib Razak sudah pening dan hilang akal memikirkan bagaimana nak pertahankan dasar lebuh raya bertol kerajaan BN yang menganiayai rakyat,â€ katanya. Menurut Pua, di bawah kerajaan PH juga kadar tol tidak akan meningkat mengikut perjanjian sehingga tamat konsesi, yang antaranya menyaksikan kadar tol bagi perjalanan dari Kuala Lumpur ke Alor Setar kekal RM45.50 pada tahun 2038, hampir separuh daripada harga yang terpaksa dibayar pengguna jika mengikut formula Najib iaitu RM82 pada tahun yang sama. Pada zaman BN kadar tol akan meningkat sekurang-kurangnya lima peratus setiap tiga tahun mengikut perjanjian konsesi, katanya sambil memberi contoh pada 1999 tempoh konsesi PLUS dilanjutkan selama 12 tahun dari 2018 hingga 2030, dengan kenaikan kadar tol 26 peratus setiap tiga hingga lima tahun sehingga 2016.

Strawberry and Cream Parfaits Ingredients â€¢250 grams strawberries, washed and quartered â€¢Sugar 2 tablespoons â€¢Fresh mint leaves (optional) â€¢200ml Brookside Dairy whipping cream â€¢2 tablespoons icing sugar â€¢1/2 tsp vanilla essence Method In a bowl add the strawberries and the sugar, stir and set aside for 30 minutes. Chill metallic or glass bowl and beaters in the freezer for 30 minutes. Once chilled, add chilled whipping cream to the chilled bowl. Whisk for a minute or so until slightly thickened. Add vanilla essence and icing sugar. Whisk on high speed for about another minute or until soft peaks are formed. Put the whipped cream in a piping bag with a star nozzle. In a glass, spoon over some of the strawberries then pipe a layer of the whipped cream. Add another layer of strawberries then the whipped cream and repeat. Garnish the top with a strawberry and a fresh mint leaves. Enjoy. #FarmFreshCulinaryChallenge #Allyouneed

Dua laluan masuk ke Shah Alam dari Lebuhraya Shah Alam (Kesas) mengalami kesesakan teruk pagi tadi susulan pelaksanaan sekatan jalan raya (SJR) oleh polis bagi menguatkuasakan Perintah Kawalan Pergerakan Bersyarat (PKPB) yang bermula hari ini. Tinjauan Bernama mendapati kesesakan trafik hampir satu kilometer di kedua-dua susur masuk di Persimpangan Hicom dari Kesas menuju Shah Alam itu susulan pelaksanaan SJR di Persiaran Kuala Selangor. Jurucakap Kesas ketika dihubungi berkata, kesesakan trafik berkenaan bagaimanapun kembali pulih setakat pukul 10.30 pagi tadi. Pada masa sama, kesesakan trafik turut dilaporkan berlaku di laluan keluar dari Plaza Tol Setia Alam menghala Subang berikutan SJR yang dilaksanakan di kawasan berkenaan namun ia kembali pulih kira-kira pukul 9 pagi tadi. Pada Isnin lepas, Menteri Kanan (Kluster Keselamatan) Datuk Seri Ismail Sabri Yaakob mengumumkan pelaksanaan PKPB di Selangor, Kuala Lumpur dan Putrajaya selama 14 hari bermula hari ini sehingga 27 Okt, berikutan peningkatan kes Covid-19.

We zijn op bezoek geweest bij mijn zoon en schoondochter die met hun kinderen in het park verbleven aangezien wij geen slaapplek hebben voor 4 personen. En het was in een woord geweldig! Ze hadden een heel leuk huisje geboekt met alles gelijkvloers aangezien ze een trap een beetje gevaarlijk vonden voor ons jongste kleinkind. We hadden geluk met het weer dat weekend en mijn man kon lekker voor het huisje vissen met onze kleinzoon terwijl ik met schoondochter en kleinkind naar het hoofdgebouw ging. Daar was van alles te doen voor de kleine, maar het leukst vond ze de ballenbak waar we met z'n drieÃ«n inzaten. Ook hebben we erg genoten in het zwembad. Het is geschikter voor hele kleine kinderen dan het hele drukke bad van een ander Center Parcs-bad in de buurt waar ze in de lente verbleven. Ik hoorde dat de huisjes momenteel stuk voor stuk gerenoveerd worden, dus ben benieuwd naar de volgende keer als ze dit park aandoen. Ze willen dan proberen een VIP-huisje te bemachtigen want die zou zelfs een wellness met een sauna hebben! Nadeel is wel dat ons kleinzoontje nu op het park wil blijven in plaats van bij opa en oma op bezoek, maar begrijpelijk ook natuurlijk, want bij ons valt weinig te beleven. En zo zijn wij er ook nog eens uit in het weekend als we 's middags op bezoek mogen komen :-)

I've occasionally eaten at the Petit Paris when dawdling through Edinburgh's Grassmarket. Sometimes the weather smiles, and there's an outdoor table (and I'm willing to pay the extra 10% service for it). This time was on a rainy Saturday, and though busy, there was a free table for one. And though busy, I thought I'd given myself enough time for a fixed price lunch special. Well, so I thought. Tables that had ordered after me were served more quickly - mains were brought, some of those diners were almost finished, others had ordered digestifs, others had finished and paid... And still I sat, table empty before me, glaiket waiters passing by, happily serving the other tables, but completely ignoring and neglecting me. Minutes ticked by. I thought I'd had allowed enough time to eat and stroll to the Traverse for a matinee, with perhaps a post-prandial pint on the way... Mais non, mes amis. And I'd ordered the stew of the day - well, I've never seen anything but boeuf bourgignon as this on the daily specials - so there was minimum prep and plating involved. They had no excuse at all, except the worst, laziest, most slovenly and neglectful service I've ever had at Petit Paris. Oh well, perhaps the two staff (and a maitre d) covering the small dining area were all suffering early onset dementia, and completely forgot my order from every glance at my table as they served others to the time they got to the kitchen. Finally I just had to leave. At last they were prompt with bringing the bourgignon to take away. I still missed the first few minutes of the matinee. Merde! The boeuf bourgignon is still in the fridge. Petit Paris can do delicious food and I'm sure this will be good enough. But good enough to remove the sour taste of their atrocious service? That I doubt. And I doubt they have surely lost a customer

Shell letter to the FT: Demand for clean energy is spur for change at Shell From Ed Daniels, Executive Vice-President, Strategy & Portfolio, Shell, The Hague, The Netherlands Your article â€œWill Shell case accelerate the shift to green energy?â€ (The Big Read, January 12) argues that Shell â€œcan still continue to expand its fossil fuel businesses while meeting its â€˜net zeroâ€™ emissions goalâ€. That is neither practically possible, nor true to our intent. Shellâ€™s intent is visible in the way the company is already, and enthusiastically, moving into low and zero-carbon energy while lowering our net carbon footprint. Shell knows it must do so today if it is to be a successful business in the future. That is the spur for change: the fact Shellâ€™s customers are increasingly demanding cleaner energy. And that is the basis for the companyâ€™s business decisions, rather than the legal action described in the article. In the online comment threads, many of your readers recognise the legal case in The Netherlands as a noisy distraction. They highlight the futility of targeting a single company, or even a single sector, to address a societal and system-wide issue like climate change. Even so, a company like Shell has a role to play in tackling climate change. We will address our own emissions and work with customers to help them reduce theirs. It is by working together that the world can reach the goals of the Paris Agreement. A major bank has moved to reduce interest rates on its business and home loans following the Reserve Bankâ€™s historic move on Tuesday. Business Cameron Micallef The Commonwealth Bank has moved to reduce business loans interest rates through the governmentâ€™s SME loan guarantee scheme by up to 51 basis points, with secured loans now at 2.99 per cent and unsecured loans at 3.99 per cent. Its fixed rate fully secured BetterBusiness loan for new three- to five-year loans will also be reduced by 50 basis points to 2.49 per cent. CBA is the first major bank to reduce its interest rates following the RBAâ€™s decision to cut the cash rate from 0.25 of a percentage point to a record low of 0.1 of a percentage point. RBA governor Philip Lowe also signalled that the board did not expect to increase the cash rate for at least three years. â€œAs we have said the whole way through this pandemic, we have a vital role to play in helping Australian businesses through the range of challenges they are facing,â€ said CBA business banking group executive Mike Vacy Lyle. â€œWe know our customers want certainty, and the cuts we have announced today will help provide some certainty in the form of highly competitive interest rates for terms of three to five years. â€œCoupled with the wide range of support measures we have rolled out over the last eight months, weâ€™re confident these offers will help many small businesses get through this challenge and back on the road to recovery and growth.â€ The new rates will take effect from 11 November. CBA will also move to reduce new four-year fixed rates for owner-occupiers by 100 basis points to 1.99 per cent â€” its lowest ever advertised home loan rate. The bank will also reduce new two and three-year fixed rate home loans for owner-occupiers to 2.14 per cent. CBA also confirmed a moratorium on forced home sales until September 2021 for customers who are unable to recommence repayments due to the pandemic.

Im Rahmen eines Produkttest haben wir die Xelsis SM7786/00 kostenlos zur Verfï¿½gung gestellt bekommen.Die Maschine bietet edle Optik und ï¿½ber den Touchscreen kï¿½nnen die Getrï¿½nke individuell angepasst werden.Neben anfï¿½nglichen Schwierigkeiten sind es diverse Kleinigkeiten die verbessert werden kï¿½nnten.Hier unsere Erfahrungen und Verbesserungsvorschlï¿½ge nach einigen Tagen der Verwendung.Auspacken:Das Gerï¿½t kam sehr gut verpackt an, nur der Styropor-Anteil dï¿½rfte in der heutigen Zeit etwas geringer ausfallen.Durch den hohen Anteil an gebï¿½rstetem Stahl wirkt die Maschine optisch sehr edel.Inbetriebnahme:Es sind nur wenige Schritte nï¿½tig, um die Maschine in Betrieb zu nehmen.Es wurde genau nach Anleitung vorgegangen, auch beim Einsetzen des Filters.Leider lieï¿½ sich die Maschine mit eingesetzem Filter nicht nutzen, Heiï¿½wasser trï¿½pfelte, die Brï¿½hgruppe quietschte bedenklich und die gemahlenen Kaffeebohnen fielen als trockenes Pulver in den Tresterbehï¿½lter. Auch ein nachgekaufter Ersatzfilter brachte kein Erfolg, ebenso wenig der Filter aus einer Maschine mit baugleichem Filter.Ohne Filter fï¿½llte sich selbst im ausgeschalteten Zustand die Auffangschale sehr schnell und lief ï¿½ber, es gab eine Pfï¿½tze unter der Maschine.Mit diesen Problemen war die Maschine daher unmittelbar nach der Inbetriebnahme zwei Mal zur Reparatur. Mï¿½glicherweise handelt es sich bei unserem Gerï¿½t um einen Einzelfall, dennoch bleibt dieser erste Eindruck hï¿½ngen.Bedienung:Neben zwei mechanischen Tasten (Ein/Aus und Start/Stop) gibt es 4 Sensor-Tasten und ein groï¿½es Touch-Display.Die 4 Sensor-Tasten sind auf englisch beschriftet, "Drinks", "Profiles", "Clean" und "Settings". Das ist nicht schlimm, aber bei einem Gerï¿½t in dieser Preisklasse wï¿½rden wir uns eine lokalisierte Bedienblende, oder ein grï¿½ï¿½eres Touch-Display wï¿½nschen, dass auch diese Bedienelemente in der gewï¿½hlten Sprache anzeigt.Unter "Drinks" sind alle verfï¿½gbaren Getrï¿½nke (zB Espresso, Latte Macchiato, Americano, Heiï¿½e Milch, Milchschaum, Heiï¿½wasser usw) enthalten. Es werden immer 4 gleichzeitig mit Bildchen angezeigt, man kann am Touchscreen durchblï¿½ttern. Wï¿½hlt man ein Getrï¿½nk, kann man es individuell anpassen, neben Wassermenge, Milchmenge auch zB Intensitï¿½t, Temperatur, Reihenfolge Milch/Kaffee. Dies geschieht mit Schiebereglern auf dem Touchscreen. Ohne Profil werden die Einstellungen zu den Getrï¿½nken nicht gespeichert werden, sprich es wird bei jeder Anwahl eines Getrï¿½nks wieder die Saeco-Standardeinstellung vorbelegt.Mï¿½chte man die Einstellungen speichern, geht dies ï¿½ber Profile. In bis zu 8 Profilen kï¿½nnen von jedem Getrï¿½nk die jeweils verfï¿½gbaren Einstellungen gespeichert werden. Im Profil sind jeweils nur die Getrï¿½nke enthalten, die man hinzufï¿½gt. Jedes Profil kann mit einem Namen versehen werden.Die Nutzung von Profilen ist sinnvoll und hilfreich, da je nach Getrï¿½nk eine Vielzahl von Einstellungen mï¿½glich sind. Allerdings wï¿½rden wir uns wï¿½nschen, ein Profil als "Standard" definieren zu kï¿½nnen. Aktuell kehrt die Maschine nach Zubereitung eines Getrï¿½nks immer in die "Drinks"-ï¿½bersicht zurï¿½ck, nicht zu einem persï¿½nlichen Profil. Wenn nun bei Besuch 4-6 gleiche Getrï¿½nke benï¿½tigt werden, muss man je 2 Getrï¿½nke jeweils 1) "Profiles" drï¿½cken, 2) entspechendes Profil wï¿½hlen, 3) das Getrï¿½nk wï¿½hlen 4) auf Start drï¿½cken. Das wï¿½rde mit einem Standard-Profil einfacher gehen, 1) und 2) wï¿½rde entfallen. Selbst wenn alle Familienmitglieder mit denselben Kaffeevorlieben/-einstellungen leben kï¿½nnen, bieten sich unterschiedliche Profile an, zB um verschieden groï¿½e Tassen/Glï¿½ser ideal nutzen zu kï¿½nnen (Einzeltassen, "Sonntagstassen" wenn Besuch kommt, Thermobecher fï¿½r unterwegs, ...) ohne jeweils Anpassungen vornehmen zu mï¿½ssen.In den Profilen kï¿½nnen Anpassungen an Getrï¿½nken sowohl einmalig (ï¿½ndern, Start drï¿½cken) oder dauerhaft (ï¿½ndern, speichern, erneut auswï¿½hlen, Start drï¿½cken) vorgenommen werden.Die Hï¿½he des Auslaufs lï¿½sst sich sehr hoch einstellen (ca 14cm), nach unten dï¿½rfte es fï¿½r Espressotassen etwas tiefer gehen, ist aber OK. Zumindest derzeit ist die Hï¿½henverstellung noch sehr schwergï¿½ngig, mï¿½glicherweise gibt sich dies nach einigen Monaten.Die jeweils zwei Auslï¿½ufe fï¿½r Milch/Heiï¿½wasser und Kaffee liegen relativ weit auseinander. Dies ist gut, wenn man zwei Getrï¿½nke gleichzeitig zubereiten mï¿½chte, je nach Espressotasse muss man zB beim Espresso Macchiato schon etwas genauer zielen, um alle 4 ï¿½ffnungen abzudecken.Nun zu Informationen zu einzelnen Getrï¿½nken, wobei Geschmack immer subjektiv ist und sowohl Geschmack als auch Crema immer von den verwendeten Bohnen abhï¿½ngt. Den Mahlgrad haben wir aktuell 1 Stufe feiner als die Voreinstellung gewï¿½hlt (Achtung, nur wï¿½hrend eines Mahlvorgangs verstellen).Espresso und Ristretto:Beides gelingt sehr gut, beim Ristretto nutzen wir die Einstellungen "Stark", "30ml", Temperatur "Hoch", "Intensiv".Dies gibt eine schï¿½ne Crema und ein gutes Aroma. Die Temperatur ist selbst bei einer dickwandigen Tasse ohne Vorwï¿½rmen OK, mit Vorwï¿½rmen oder in einem Doppelwandigen Espressoglas richtig heiï¿½. Auch bei Temperatureinstellung "Hoch" wird der Espresso nicht bitter. Latte Macchiato: Die Milch lï¿½uft erstaunlich schnell durch das Milchsystem, der Schaum ist dennoch offenporig/fest. Temperatur ist (bei Temperatureinstellung "hoch") gut, wenn auch nicht heiï¿½.Die Optik ist nicht ganz perfekt, die heiï¿½e Milch unten und der Espresso vermischen sich von selbst, oben bleibt aber ein hoher Anteil festen Milchschaums.Geschmacklich gibt es nichts auszusetzen. Auffï¿½llig: Der Milchtank hat eine Skala mit ml-Angabe, bei der Maschine kann die Milchmenge in ml angegeben werden. Dies passt nicht zusammen: Bei Einstellung 300ml an der Maschine werden nur ca 230ml Milch verarbeitet, auch der Milchschaum hat ein Volumen von weniger als 300ml. Mit den Einstellungen "Stark", Kaffee 50ml, Milch 300ml, Temperatur "hoch" haben wir bisher gute Erfahrungen gemacht.Nur Milchschaum:Es gibt sowohl die Mï¿½glichkeit "Heiï¿½e Milch" als auch "Milchschaum" separat zu erzeugen, ohne Umwege ï¿½ber Mischgetrï¿½nke. Somit kï¿½nnen auch Familienmitglieder, die keinen Kaffee mï¿½gen, die Maschine mitnutzen.Der Milchschaum hat Trinktemperatur, ist also nicht sehr heiï¿½. Auch hier ist die ml-Angabe nicht hilfreich: Bei zwei Portionen zu je 180ml werden nur etwa 200ml Milch aus dem Milchtank gezogen.Nun zur Reinigung der Maschine.Reinigung Milchkreislauf:Einige Teile kï¿½nnen direkt an der Maschine mit Dampf gereinigt werden, zB der Schlauch und das Rohr mittels "HygieSteam".Alle Teile sollte man trotzdem in kï¿½rzerem Abstand von der Maschine entfernen und mit Spï¿½lmittel reinigen. Die Klappe am Auslauf hat einen magnetischen Verschluss. Ist sie geï¿½ffnet, werden die Milchgetrï¿½nke im Touchscreen deaktiviert.Die ï¿½ffnung am Milchbehï¿½lter ist verschlieï¿½bar, so kann der Behï¿½lter im Kï¿½hlschrank aufbewahrt werden. Der Milchbehï¿½lter kann in der Spï¿½lmaschine gereinigt werden, wir reinigen ihn schonender von Hand.Reinigung Wassertank:Der Wassertank lï¿½sst sich innen relativ gut reinigen, ï¿½blicherweise sollte ein Durchspï¿½len mit klarem Wasser genï¿½gen.Die Bauform und Handhabung des Wassertanks ist nicht optimal. An der Front lï¿½sst sich der volle Wassertank schlecht halten und einsetzen.Reinigung Auffangschalen:Die Auffangschale ist relativ flach, aber sehr lang. Beim Herausnehmen muss man daher aufpassen, dass nichts ï¿½berlï¿½uft. Die Auffangschale fï¿½llt sich sehr schnell, auch wenn man wï¿½hrend des Spï¿½lens beim Ein-/Ausschalten immer eine Tasse unter den Auslauf stellt. Es gibt nur eine mechanische Fï¿½llstandsanzeige, keine elektronische. Gemï¿½ï¿½ Anleitung soll man die Auffangschale mindestens 1x tï¿½glich leeren und reinigen. Das Tropfgitter fï¿½r die Kaffeetassen wird mit zwei Magneten festgehalten, das ist praktisch. Der Behï¿½lter fï¿½r Kaffeetrester ist unabhï¿½ngig von der Auffangschale fï¿½r Wasser entnehmbar. Er hat am hinteren Rand eine Gummilippe, daher ist die Reinigung etwas aufwï¿½ndig.Die "HygieSteam"-Reinigung fï¿½r den Milchschlauch ist zwar praktisch, dazu muss aber der Schlauch mit Metallstab seitlich neben der Maschine in eine entsprechende ï¿½ffnung der Auffangschale gesteckt werden. Beim Leeren der Auffangschale muss man dann schauen, wo man den Schlauch samt Metallrohr ablegt. Weiterhin muss man aufpassen, dass der Milchbehï¿½lter links nicht zu nahe an der Maschine steht, sonst kï¿½nnte man ihn beim Herausziehen der Auffangschale herunterwerfen. Reinigung der Brï¿½hgruppe:Die Brï¿½hgruppe wird rechts entnommen, dazu muss die Gehï¿½useseite komplett aufgeklappt werden, was sehr viel freien Platz rechts neben der Maschine benï¿½tigt, ï¿½ber 30cm. Nachdem die Brï¿½hgruppe wï¿½chentlich entnommen und unter klarem Wasser ausgespï¿½lt werden soll, ist diese Anordnung nicht optimal.Reinigung Gehï¿½use:Dank des hohen Anteils an gebï¿½rstem Edelstahl zieht das Gehï¿½use wenig Staub an. Ein groï¿½er Vorteil gegenï¿½ber Kunststoffgehï¿½usen. Die Oberflï¿½chen lassen sich problemlos reinigen, feuchter Lappen mit etwas Spï¿½lmittel genï¿½gen. Einzig mit der Klappe zum Pulverfach muss man etwas aufpassen.Automatische Abschaltung:Die Maschine stellt sich nach einstellbarer Zeit (in Stufen zw. 15min und 180min) selbst ab, dabei wird - wie auch beim Einschalten - eine Spï¿½lung des Kaffeekreislaufs vorgenommen.Tassen vorwï¿½rmen:Die Tassenablage vor dem Bohnenbehï¿½lter ist relativ groï¿½, aber nicht beheizt. Sie wird im Betrieb nur ein wenig warm.Daher sind speziell dickwandige Espressotassen am besten ï¿½ber die Heiï¿½wasserfunktion vorzuwï¿½rmen.

Tinjauan: Marlboro adalah merek rokok terlaris di dunia. Merek ini dinamai Great Marlborough Street, lokasi Pabrik London aslinya. Philip Morris Company, produsen rokok yang berbasis di London, mendirikan anak perusahaan di New York pada tahun 1902 untuk menjual beberapa merek rokoknya, termasuk Marlboro. Pada tahun 1924 Philip Morris meluncurkan merek Marlboro sebagai rokok wanita. Pada tahun 1930, rokok Marlboro memiliki ujung gading yang tahan minyak untuk mencegah lunturnya lipstik wanita; pada tahun 1940 sebuah "Tip Kecantikan" merah untuk menyembunyikan noda lipstik yang tidak sedap dipandang. Marlboro menjadi merek rokok untuk pria pada tahun 1954. Selama tahun 1950-an majalah Reader's Digest menerbitkan serangkaian artikel yang mengaitkan merokok dengan kanker paru-paru. Philip Morris, dan perusahaan rokok lainnya memperhatikan dan masing-masing mulai memasarkan rokok filter. Marlboro baru dengan ujung yang disaring diluncurkan pada tahun 1955. Slogan (1924): Â«Ringan seperti MeiÂ» Properti: Philip Morris USA Inc. - Altria Group Inc. Marlboro ad 1938 Iklan rokok Marlboro (1938, ujung gading melindungi bibir) Paket Marlboro 1940 Rokok Marlboro "Beauty Tip" (1940) Rokok memiliki "Tip Kecantikan" merah untuk menyembunyikan noda lipstik yang tidak sedap dipandang. Marlboro ad 1941 Iklan rokok Marlboro (1941, A Beauty Tip) Kotak Marlboro 1955 Rokok Marlboro "Flip-Top Box" (1955) Diperkenalkan kembali dengan filter "selectrate" ujung gabus dan dalam Kotak Flip-Top.
